		<startup>
			<splash-texture>Aircraft/Lockheed-Martin-FA-22A-Raptor/F-22-splash.png</splash-texture>
		</startup>

			<gui>
				<style>
				<colors>
					<splash-screen>
						<red>0.57</red>
						<green>0.60</green>
						<blue>0.60</blue>
					</splash-screen>
				</colors>
				</style>
			</gui>

			<sound>
				<path>Aircraft/Lockheed-Martin-FA-22A-Raptor/F-22-sound.xml</path>
			</sound>

			<help>
				<title>F-22</title>
				<key>
					<name>Home</name>
					<desc>Increase elevator trim</desc>
				</key>
				<key>
					<name>End</name>
					<desc>Decrease elevator trim</desc>
				</key>

				<key>
					<name>]</name>
					<desc>Lower flaps</desc>
				</key>
				<key>
					<name>[</name>
					<desc>Raise flaps</desc>
				</key>
				
				<key>
					<name>B</name>
					<desc>Brakes</desc>
				</key>
				<key>
					<name>g</name>
					<desc>landing gear UP</desc>
				</key>
				<key>
					<name>G</name>
					<desc>landing gear DOWN</desc>
				</key>
				
				<key>
					<name>ctrl+b</name>
					<desc>toggle speed brakes</desc>
				</key>

	
	<line>FUEL: First time you fly the F-22 Raptor, the tanks have a 10 percent level. Be sure you fill all tanks starting from forward to after</line>
	<line>Take off:</line>
	<line>Release the park brake and set the throttle  around 20 percent RPM and raise flaps one time</line>
	<line>Rotate at around 20 knots and align with the runway, and then full throttle</line>	
	<line>rotate at  around 180 knots and  pull back the stick </line>
	<line>keep a reasonable pitch</line>
	<line>Be carefull with the afterburner, because the vectors will lift the F22's nose very much</line>
	<line>The vectors are controled by the yoke</line>
	<line>Landing:</line>
	<line>Reduce speed around 250 knots and set full flaps landing gear down</line>
	<line>AOA minus 10 degrees</line>
	<line>Final approach speed 160 knots</line>
	<line>Touch at 150 knots AOA  +10 degrees </line>
	<line>Press "b" to brakes and </line>
	<line>Have fun</line>

			</help>

